        "authorAssociation": "MEMBER",
        "title": "Fixes connection issue in Firefox",
        "bodyText": "Underlying connection in ethers JsonRpcProvider had been consistently failing. It appeared that the HTTP version was being incorrectly set. Instead of POST ... HTTP/2 the request would read POST ... undefined. Overriding the send function and using axios fixes the issue. If there's something lighter weight happy to check it out. Tested in Firefox and Chrome.\nAlso added a null check in setTokens in src/tokens/index.js.",
        "labels": {
            "nodes": []
        },
